  "content": " report it through the International Material Data System directly. Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) IMDS (International Material Data System) Company ID# is 223417. Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA)’s acceptance criteria are based on IMDS (International Material Data System) recommendations. Supplier  must be aware of updates to the GADSL (Global Automotive Declarable Substance List) and ensure that information submitted is correct and comply with the recommendations of the IMDS (International Material Data System) system. Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) can request clarifications and corrections to previously submitted and accepted IMDS (International Material Data System) data. EU REACH (Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals) Regulation (EC) No. 1907/2006 The Supplier  must fulfill all obligations due to Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals. This includes communication obligations of SVHC (Substances of Very High Concern) in articles, even for spare parts and packaging. Suppliers located outside the European Union have to name an Only Representative (OR) if they deliver products defined as ´substances´ or ´mixtures into the area of validity of the REACH (Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals) regulation. The OR ensures that the REACH (Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals) obligations are met. The OR’s name has to be notified to the Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA). EU REACH (Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals) SVHC (Substances of Very High Concern) All substances added to the Candidate List and present in products above 0.1% w/w must be notified to Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA). When the Candidate List is updated, and new Substances of Very High Concern (SVHC (Substances of Very High Concern)) are added then the obligation for suppliers to inform their customers becomes immediately effective. The supplier is requested not to use SVHC (Substances of Very High Concern) in articles and mixtures delivered to Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA). EU REACH (Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals) Annex XIV (Authorization List) Supplier  shall not use any substance included in this list. EU REACH (Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals) Annex XVII (Restriction List) Supplier  shall only use substances from the list if it complies with the restrictions. KKDIK (Kimyasalların, Kaydı, Değerlendirilmesi, İzni ve Kısıtlanması (i.e., Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals)) Regulation Official Gazette No. 30105 The Supplier  must fulfill all obligations due to Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals. This includes communication obligations of SVHC (Substances of Very High Concern) in articles, even for spare parts and packaging. Suppliers located outside Turkey have to name an Only Representative (OR) if they deliver products defined as ´substances´ or ´mixtures into the area of validity of the KKDIK (Kimyasalların, Kaydı, Değerlendirilmesi, İzni ve Kısıtlanması (i.e., Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals)) regulation. The OR ensures that the KKDIK (Kimyasalların, Kaydı, Değerlendirilmesi, İzni ve Kısıtlanması (i.e., Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals)) obligations are met. The OR’s name must be notified to Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA). KKDIK (Kimyasalların, Kaydı, Değerlendirilmesi, İzni ve Kısıtlanması (i.e., Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals)) SVHC (Substances of Very High Concern) All substances added to the Candidate List and present in products above 0.1% w/w must be notified to Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA). When the Candidate List is updated, and new Substances of Very High Concern (SVHC (Substances of Very High Concern)) are added, then the obligation for suppliers to"
