  "content": " requirements, including a signed PSW (Part Submission Warrant). Where PSW (Part Submission Warrant)’s must be updated on a regular basis, according to OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) requirements e.g. annual lay-outs, suppliers will be notified by SDDC (Supplier  Development Documentation Center) to submit updated PPAP (Production Part Approval Process) documentation free of charge. Initial Samples must be sent as scheduled and always before the start of volume production. Samples must be identified with “Initial Sample” labels and accompanied by appropriate documentation. Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) Purchasing, SQE (Supplier  Quality Engineer) or SDDC (Supplier  Development Documentation Center) may define samples delivery to the relevant Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) `Pilot Plant`. Unless otherwise specified by Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA), the submission of PPAP (Production Part Approval Process) shall be according AIAG (Automotive Industry Action Group) Level 3 or VDA2 with all applicable deliverables submitted. 4.1 Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) Designed Products For all Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) designed products / parts and upon request of Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA), APQP (Advanced Product  Quality Planning) or VDA (Verband der Automobilindustrie (German Automotive Association)) MLA (Maturity Level Assurance (acc. to VDA (Verband der Automobilindustrie (German Automotive Association))))/RGA methodology, must be applied by the supplier and follow upped by ASQE (Advanced Supplier  Quality Engineer). Project Management must be tracked via the Integrated Supplier  Quality Management System. Supplier  shall register to Integrated Supplier  Quality Management System if required. In that case, Integrated Supplier  Quality Management System -membership fee, if applicable, is at the cost of the supplier. Projects will be kicked off by the SQE (Supplier  Quality Engineer) who specifies APQP (Advanced Product  Quality Planning) and PPAP (Production Part Approval Process) scope. Additionally, a Process Sign Off (including VDA (Verband der Automobilindustrie (German Automotive Association)) 6.3 Process Audit, R@R, Capacity Check) must be carried out by the SQE (or by supplier) before initial sample submission, in order to validate the process and product in accordance with IATF 16949 and any other OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) / Customer specific requirement. See also Section 4.2. 4.2 Customer Specific Requirements Supplier  is responsible to follow and implement latest revision of Customer Specific Requirement, available on https://www.iatfglobaloversight.org/oem-requirements/customer-specific-requirements/. General customer specific requirements included in this Manual shall be implemented. Additional customer specific requirements issued by Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) customers will be communicated on a project basis. Their application will be subject to an agreement between Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) and the supplier. EA-QM-xx-M-740, Rev New, 11/12/2024 4.3 Reasons for Initial Samples The PPA (Production Process and Product  Approval)/PPAP (Production Part Approval Process) Approval Process is required if any of the following changes apply at the supplier or sub-supplier: • if a product is ordered for the first time • after the supplier has changed a subcontractor • for all affected characteristics after any product modification • for all affected characteristics following"
