uality Reporting System for Components) portal, identifying containment actions (3D) within 24 hours. The appropriate Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) SQA (Supplier  Quality Assurance Engineer) personnel responsible for handling the concern must review and approve the proposed supplier actions. 7.1.5 Permanent Corrective Action Suppliers must provide Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) with 8D root cause analysis, using appropriate Quality Tools, as 5 Whys or Ishikawa Diagram, the report must be submitted within 10 working days with an 8D report detailing complete corrective action. A corrective action-timing plan (in conjunction with 7.1.4 above), must be submitted to the appropriate SQA (Supplier  Quality Assurance Engineer) personnel, who must approve the proposed plan / actions. 7.1.6 Customer Line Returns, Warranty Returns to Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) and NTF Process If supplier responsibility is identified,"
